item.title: Heeled Sandals
item.dc:creator: lord
item.content:encoded: Offering irresistible fashion and fast off the catwalk styles, New Look joins the ASOS round up of great British high street brands. Bringing forth their award-winning clothing collection of dresses, jeans and jersey basics alongside a punchy edit of accessories. Go glam with skater and bodycon dresses or keep casual with high waisted jeans and biker boots.
item.excerpt:encoded: Sandals by New Look Leather-look upper Pin buckle ankle strap Platform sole High, chunky heel Avoid contact with liquids Heel Height: 9cm/3.5"

item.title: Backpack in Navy
item.dc:creator: lord
item.content:encoded: Herschel produces quality built backpacks inspired by vintage mountaineering equipment, American heritage and world travel. With a passion for individuality and personal style, Herschel have adapted their original designs to fit a new generation, bringing forth a collection of shoppers, holdalls and bumbags with a modern fit, shape and feel.
item.excerpt:encoded: Bag by Herschel Canvas fabric Flap front pocket, side zip detail Flap top Contrast pin buckle straps Grab handle Adjustable shoulder straps Do not wash 100% Polyester H: 48cm/19" W: 38cm/15" D: 12cm/5"

item.title: BOSS Blazer
item.dc:creator: lord
item.content:encoded: BOSS Orange is a contemporary offshoot of the Hugo Boss brand. The brand uses modern materials, matching them with state of the art design to make functional, timeless and modern products. BOSS Orange specialises in watches and accessories, creating goods that embody the youthful ethos of the brand.
item.excerpt:encoded: Soft-touch marl jersey fabric Notched lapel Two button opening Towelling interior Regular fit - true to size Machine wash 100% Cotton Our model wears a size Medium and is 183cm/6'0" tall

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: Awesome! The color is exactly what I like <3

item.title: Bomber With Trims
item.dc:creator: lord
item.content:encoded: Danish fashion house,Moda, made their mark on the fashion scene by using top models Kate Moss and Gisele Bundchen in their marketing campaigns. With emphasis on quality, affordable and inspiring clothing; their range of statement dresses and tailored garments embrace the essence of current trends whilst maintaining a practical edge. Meanwhile their lingerie collection,Moda Intimates, channels the brand's feminine aesthetic, with soft lace trims, ditsy florals and candy coloured prints adorning a selection of bras and briefs.
item.excerpt:encoded: Jacket by ASOS Soft-touch jersey fabric Ribbed collar Press stud fastening Side slant pockets Ribbed trim with jacquard Regular fit - true to size Machine wash 56% Cotton, 44% Polyester Our model wears a size Medium and is 185.5cm/6'1" tall

item.title: Jewel Dress
item.dc:creator: lord
item.content:encoded: Based in both London and Delhi, Needle & Thread specialise in beautiful hand-embellished designs, mixing traditional Indian beading with contemporary London styling. Under the creative direction of Hannah Coffin, Needle & Thread present a luxe and eclectic collection that mixes vintage-inspired embroidery and glossy sequins across glittering mini skirts, bodycon and maxi dresses.
item.excerpt:encoded: Evening dress by Needle & Thread 56% Polyester, 44% Acrylic Textured jacquard fabric Lined top Hand embellished collar Pleated skirt design

item.title: Top with Sleeves
item.dc:creator: lord
item.content:encoded: Directional, exciting and diverse, the ASOS Collection makes and breaks the fashion rules. Scouring the globe for inspiration, our London based Design Team is inspired by fashions most covetable trends; providing you with a cutting edge wardrobe season upon season.
item.excerpt:encoded: T-shirt by ASOS Collection - Made from cotton blend jersey - Scoop neckline - Full length sleeves - Regular fit

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: Wow! I like it so much!

item.title: Polo Shirt In Jersey
item.dc:creator: lord
item.content:encoded: Designed in-house in our London studio by our dedicated menswear team, ASOS offer a range of mens clothing designed and created exclusively for ASOS.
item.excerpt:encoded: Polo shirt by ASOS Made from cotton Three button placket Ribbed cuffs Regular fit

wp:comment.wp:comment_content: It's so nice, I want it so much ;)

item.title: Hooded Jacket
item.dc:creator: lord
item.content:encoded: High street favourites River Island are known for the unique touches they add to their directional pieces of mens clothing. River Island offer a complete menswear range that covers everything from the newest cuts in jeans to graphic print t-shirts and knitwear.
item.excerpt:encoded: Jacket by River Island Durable, cotton blend fabric Funnel neck with hood Contrast panels to rear and sleeve ends Concealed zip and press stud closure Multiple front pockets Regular fit - true to size 79% Cotton, 21% Cotton Our model wears a size Medium and is 183cm/6'0" tall

item.title: Esprit Shirt
item.dc:creator: lord
item.content:encoded: Esprit was founded by Susie and Doug Tompkins from the back of their station wagon in countercultural '60s San Francisco. From these bohemian beginnings, the label has risen to become an iconic international brand, synonymous with fresh, youthful style. Look to Esprit's menswear line for a casual and crisply sporty collection of slim-fit cotton chinos alongside collegiate-style blazers, polo shirts and preppy knitwear.
item.excerpt:encoded: T-shirt by Esprit Made from pure 100% cotton Crew neck Printed design to front Short sleeves Regular fit

item.title: Ben Sherman T-Shirt
item.dc:creator: lord
item.content:encoded: Adopted by the Mod movement of the 1960s, Ben Sherman channel their Mod roots to a contemporary range of menswear, including everything from their iconic check shirts to polos and print t-shirts.
item.excerpt:encoded: Print T-shirt by Ben Sherman 100% Cotton Breathable, jersey fabric Crew neck Print to front Regular fit - true to size Our model wears a size Medium and is 183cm/6'0" tall Machine wash

item.title: Long Sleeve
item.dc:creator: lord
item.content:encoded: On seeing the word 're-play' flash up on screen during the 1978 Argentinian World Cup, Italian founder Claudio Buziol decided it would make the perfect name for a clothing line. Alluding to the world of vintage by reinterpreting clothing from the past in a contemporary way, Replay creates a line of hand crafted denim jeans, t-shirts, shirts, jackets and sweats all in Replay's signature style.
item.excerpt:encoded: Long sleeved t-shirt by Replay Made from 100% cotton Lightweight and breathable fabric Crew neck Large print to chest Full length sleeves Regular fit

item.title: Farah Vintage Shirt
item.dc:creator: lord
item.content:encoded: From their birth in the 1920s, Farah Vintage has been adopted by subcultures across the board; from Mods to Skins and Rockabillies. Renowned for their classic canvas slacks and sharply cut tailoring, Farah Vintage retains its heritage across a collection of slim fitting polo shirts and checked flannel shirts.
item.excerpt:encoded: Shirt by Farah Vintage Soft-touch, crisp fabric Point collar Button placket Slim fit - cut closely to the body Machine wash 100% Cotton Our model wears a size Medium and is 183cm/6'0" tall

item.title: The Comedy of Errors
item.dc:creator: lord
item.content:encoded: Traditionally, the play has been dated quite early, and has often been seen as Shakespeare's first comedy, perhaps his first play. However, stylistic and linguistic analysis has placed it closer to the composition of Richard II and Romeo and Juliet, both of which were written in 1594 or 1595.

item.title: Henry VI, Part 1
item.dc:creator: lord
item.content:encoded: Philip Henslowe saw a new play entitled Harey Vj, but gives no further information. In August, Thomas Nashe published Piers Penniless his Supplication to the Devil, in which he refers to a play he had recently seen featuring a rousing depiction of Lord Talbot, a major character in 1 Henry VI. Most critics take Nashe's reference to Talbot as proof that the play Henslowe saw was 1 Henry VI.

item.title: Titus Andronicus
item.dc:creator: lord
item.content:encoded: According to the title page of the 1594 quarto, the play had been performed by Pembroke's Men, a company which ceased performing in September 1593. As such, the play must have been composed some time prior to September. Additionally, it is unlikely to have been written later than June 1592, as that was when the London theatres were closed due to an outbreak of plague.

item.title: The Merchant of Venice
item.dc:creator: lord
item.content:encoded: The play was obviously in existence by 1598, however, other evidence places its date of composition as earlier, probably 1596. Shakespeare's source for the casket subplot is believed to have been Richard Robinson's translation of the Gesta romanorum, which wasn't published until late 1595.

item.title: The Merry Wives of Windsor
item.dc:creator: lord
item.content:encoded: Textual evidence and certain topical allusions suggest the play was composed as a specially commissioned piece for a Garter Feast, possibly the Feast on 23 April 1597. It is theorised that Shakespeare interrupted his composition of 2 Henry IV somewhere around Act 3-Act 4, so as to concentrate on writing Merry Wives.

item.title: The tragicall historie of Hamlet
item.dc:creator: lord
item.content:encoded: Because the versions of Hamlet which appeared in 1603, in 1604 and in the First Folio of 1623 differ so much from one another, dating the play is exceptionally difficult. There is also the problem of the Ur-Hamlet, a possible source used by Shakespeare, now lost. Others however, feel that Ur-Hamlet was most likely an early draft.

item.title: Historye of Kinge Lear
item.dc:creator: lord
item.content:encoded: The play must have been written by late 1606. Additionally, scholars generally agree that the play is indebted to Samuel Harsnett's Declaration of Egregious Popish Impostures and John Florio's 1603 translation of Montaigne's Essays., placing the date of composition as somewhere between March 1603 and December 1606.A further possible source for the play has evoked some disagreement however.
